In simple terms, the mean of Abstraction is to show the necessary things to the user 
and hide the details. In abstraction, the user will able to access only those parts 
of information that are necessary for them. This is also known as data abstraction in java.

Abstract class: is a restricted class that cannot be used to create objects (to access it,
 it must be inherited from another class).
 
 Abstract method: can only be used in an abstract class, and it does not have a body. 
 The body is provided by the subclass (inherited from).